                <p style=3D"text-align: center;">As a jeweller, it=E2=80=99=
s important to understand the hardness and durability of <a href=3D"https:/=
/www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by-gemstone" style=3D"background-color: =
initial;">gemstones</a>. This helps you determine what designs suit particu=
lar stones, how to look after them and how to prevent them from being damag=
ed.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"text-align: center;">Find out more about the Mohs =
Hardness Scale - used in geology to measure the scratch resistance of stone=
s - not to be confused with the toughness of the stone!</p><h3 style=3D"tex=
t-align: center;">What Is The Mohs Hardness Scale?</h3><p style=3D"text-ali=
gn: center;">The Mohs Hardness Scale was developed by German mineralogist, =
Friedrich Mohs in 1812. The scale consists of 10 readily available minerals=
 of particular hardness, ranging from soft minerals such as talc all the wa=
y up to hard minerals such as diamond. The scale is used to compare the scr=
atch resistance of a mineral against these common materials, in order to me=
asure the hardness.</p><p style=3D"text-align: center;">Gemstone Size Guide=
: Image features our handy gemstone size guide, which is a double sized lam=
inated A4 sheet with accurate sizes for cabochon and faceted stones. Not on=
ly that, it also includes other helpful information such as the Mohs hardne=
ss scale, birthstones by month, bezel length guide and a list of gemstones =
we regularly stock as a useful reference.</p><p class=3D"r-button-white r-b=
utton-round-lg" style=3D"text-align: center;"><a href=3D"https://www.kernow=
craft.com/product/gemstone-size-guide">SHOP SIZE GUIDE</a></p>
