                </svg>
        </a>


            </div>


            <div class=3D"asset asset-text asset-force-padding">
                <h3 style=3D"text-align: center;">Toughness Of Stones</h3><=
p style=3D"text-align: center;">Although a stone may feature high on the Mo=
h=E2=80=99s Hardness Scale, this does not&nbsp;mean that the stone is tough=
 and won=E2=80=99t break - no gemstone is perfect, not even a diamond!</p><=
p style=3D"text-align: center;">Toughness is rated from poor, fair, good, e=
xcellent to exceptional.</p><p style=3D"text-align: center;">Although&nbsp;=
<a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by-gemstone/diamond">d=
iamond</a> is the hardest natural substance on earth, it is rated as =E2=80=
=98good=E2=80=99 for toughness as if it is hit at a certain angle, it can f=
racture and cause the stone to break.&nbsp;Corundum (such as ruby and sapph=
ire) however are the most durable stones, measuring 8 on the Mohs Scale and=
 considered =E2=80=98excellent=E2=80=99 for toughness.</p><p style=3D"text-=
align: center;">If you're wondering which stones are best for everyday wear=
 such as an engagement ring,&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/pr=
oducts/shop-by-gemstone/sapphire" style=3D"background-color: initial;">sapp=
hire</a>,&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by-gems=
tone/ruby" style=3D"background-color: initial;">ruby</a> and&nbsp;<a href=
=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by-gemstone/diamond" style=3D=
"background-color: initial;">diamond</a> are wonderful choices.</p><p style=
=3D"text-align: center;">The toughness of a stone relies on its internal st=
ructure - for instance, crystal formed gemstones are weaker due to the incl=
usions within the stone. If the stone is knocked at a particular angle, it =
can be chipped or fractured.&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/pr=
oducts/shop-by-gemstone/emerald" style=3D"background-color: initial;">Emera=
ld</a> is an example of a brittle stone, which has many natural inclusions =
and therefore can easily break.&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com=
/products/shop-by-gemstone/jade" style=3D"background-color: initial;">Jadei=
te Jade and Nephrite Jade</a>, on the other hand, measures low on the Mohs =
Hardness Scale at a 6.5 but is rated exceptional for toughness, due to its =
strong internal crystal structure.</p><p><strong></strong></p>
            </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class=3D"col-xs-12 col-sm-6">



                                    <div class=3D"column column-6084-1 alig=
n-assets-top has-fill">


            <div class=3D"asset asset-image">
        <a class=3D"asset-zoom" href=3D"https://img.kernowcraft.com/cdn-cgi=
/image/w=3D2724,q=3D90,f=3Dauto/original/aa521083/105823.jpg">
            <img src=3D"https://img.kernowcraft.com/cdn-cgi/image/w=3D1362,=
q=3D90,f=3Dauto/original/aa521083/105823.jpg" width=3D"3000" height=3D"3000=
" loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"img-responsive" alt=3D"amethyst sale image 1 z.=
jpg">

                <svg class=3D"icon icon-xs icon-zoom">
                    <use xlink:href=3D"/Resources/dist/img/symbol/svg/sprit=
e.symbol.svg?v=3D1#plus"></use>
                </svg>
        </a>


            </div>


            <div class=3D"asset asset-text asset-force-padding">
                <h3 style=3D"text-align: center;">Stability Of Stones</h3><=
p style=3D"text-align: center;">Other <g>factors</g> to take into considera=
tion are external elements such as light, heat and chemicals which can caus=
e a stone to change colour or even break.</p><p style=3D"text-align: center=
;"><a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by-gemstone/amethys=
t">Amethyst</a> and <a href=3D"https://www.kernowcraft.com/products/shop-by=
-gemstone/citrine">citrine</a> <g>for example</g> are both stones that are =
sensitive to light and if exposed for long periods of time can become dull.=
 This is why gemstones should always be stored suitably and separately to a=
void any damage. Temperature is also something to consider as sudden temper=
ature changes can prompt thermal shock, causing fractures and cracks. </p><=
p style=3D"text-align: center;">When wearing gemstone jewellery, we come in=
to contact with chemicals on a daily basis, so it=E2=80=99s important to re=
member that gemstones can be damaged due to this exposure. Examples include=
 cleaning, swimming, showering, using hair spray and perfume - so always be=
 mindful of your jewellery when doing activities<g>.</g></p><p style=3D"tex=
t-align: center;"><g>Whe</g>n it comes to cleaning jewellery, a small dish =
of soapy water is all you need. If you use an ultrasonic cleaner (used to c=
lean jewellery), the tiny vibrations may cause a stone to break or even los=
e its colouring if heat treated so always check whether the jewellery you w=
ish to clean is suitable.</p>
            </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style=3D"position: relative" class=3D"section section-6082 ali=
gn-row-stretch align-columns-top">


            <div class=3D"container-fluid">
                <div class=3D"section-inner">
                    <div class=3D"row">
